This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing tasks, specifically text summarization, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also heavily utilizes deep learning techniques, such as pretrained encoders and transformers, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and fine-tuning of models, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
